Indians considerate flyers, hate seat kickers, misbehaving passengers: Survey

A recent survey by Expedia Flight Etiquette reveals that Indians find rear-seat kickers, boozers and loud passengers most annoying in a flight. However, they are tolerant towards flirting singles and amorous couples, and are considerate towards fellow passengers. Here’s more… 
